<font color="#FF0000">TO CHRIS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Mar 15 19:20:08 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chris hang on to those ideals of yours.<br><br>
If it were not for our exporting of weaponry our trade deficit would be much worse than it is now.<br><br>
Bob Dole said during Desert Shield that we were in the Gulf because of &quot;oil&quot;. George Bush said it best by declaring we were there to protect our &quot;way of life&quot;.<br><br>
In 1973, during the first oil crisis we were warned that it was necessary to develop alternative energy sources or supplies. Almost 25 years have gone by and we are still very dependent on Middle East oil. Yes, we have learned to be more efficient, but the need for foreign oil is still great.<br><br>
Who is to blame? Look in the mirror. We all are. <br><br>
Our prominent politicians during Desert Shield, along with a tremendous, consenting, majority demonstrated that it is acceptible to send Americans to die in the Middle East, rather than accept a lower standard of living.<br><br>

